{"article_id":"HuxxES9t5n806hE8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A New York Police Department officer wears a protective mask during the coronavirus outbreak in New York City , March 20 , 2020 .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"( Andrew Kelly/Reuters )","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"On the menu today :","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"a report","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"that the CDC might want us to start wearing masks after all ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"some encouraging signs about America ' s fevers from a thermometer system","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"that the NSA would envy ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"how police ought to approach the issue of defiant religious gatherings during a pandemic ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"and a recent Morning Jolt reaches a milestone .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Are We About to Be Urged to Start Wearing Masks ?","depth":3},{"id":10,"text":"Saturday , Dr. Matt McCarthy , an assistant professor at the medical school of Cornell University , tweeted ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"\" CDC guidance on masks","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"expected to change in next 10 days .","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"Americans will be advised to wear masks in everyday life .","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"Current recommendation is for high-risk groups only . \"","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"But later that day , the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention responded to his tweet ,","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"appearing to shoot down that idea .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"\" CDC does not have updated guidance","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"scheduled to come out on this topic. \"","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"They referred to the current guidance ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"which is :","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"But this morning , the Washington Post reports the same thing","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"McCarthy claimed :","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Officials at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention are considering altering the official guidance","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"to encourage people to take measures","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"to cover their faces amid the coronavirus pandemic ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"according to a federal official","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"who spoke on the condition of anonymity","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"because it is an ongoing matter of internal discussion","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"and nothing has been finalized .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"CDC guidance on masks remains under development ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"the federal official said .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"The official said","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"the new guidance would make clear","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"that the general public should not use medical masks","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"- including surgical and N95 masks -","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"that are in desperately short supply","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"and needed by health-care workers .","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"Instead , the recommendation under consideration calls for using do-it-yourself cloth coverings ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"according to a second official","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"who shared that thinking on a personal Facebook account .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"It would be a way","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"to help \" flatten the curve , \"","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"the official noted .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"I realize","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"the CDC is dealing with an unprecedented situation ,","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"and we ' re still learning about this virus .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"But either masks help","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"or they don ' t ;","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"if they don ' t help at all ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"it doesn ' t make sense that they would be needed by health-care workers .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"( I ' m reminded of the head miner","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"confronting the officials in the HBO miniseries Chernobyl ,","depth":15},{"id":53,"text":"scoffing at a not-so-persuasive claim","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"that the masks would offer protection from inhaling radioactive dust .","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"\" If these worked ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"you would be wearing them . \" )","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"There are a lot of problems with the concept of the \" noble lie , \"","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"and a big one is that it makes it harder for the truth to come out later","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"- and","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"once it does ,","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"the authority ' s credibility is damaged .","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"If you tell the public","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"that masks don ' t work","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"because you don ' t want them running out","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"and buying them","depth":16},{"id":66,"text":"and hoarding them ,","depth":16},{"id":67,"text":"some people are not going to believe you","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"if you come back with a different message later .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"If the CDC wants people to start wearing masks ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"they ' re going to have to persuade a chunk of the public","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that will instinctively say ,","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"\" Why should I wear one ?","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"I heard","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"those things don ' t work . \"","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Back in late February , Vox reported","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"\" most health experts said","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"there ' s no good evidence","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"to support the use of face masks","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"for preventing this disease in the general population , \"","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"and quoted one professor","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"as saying ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"\" wearing a mask can also appear ' overly alarmist . ' \"","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Because we sure as heck didn ' t want people seeming alarmist about the coronavirus back in late February ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"now did we ?","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"America Is Having Fewer Fevers .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Is That a Sign","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"We ' re Winning ?","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Kinsa Health produces Internet-connected thermometers","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"and is collecting and analyzing all of that data","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"coming in every day .","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"It ' s fascinating ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"as long as you ' re okay with your thermometer doing the kind of consistent surveillance of the details of American lives","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"that we usually associate with , say , the NSA .","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"To identify clusters of coronavirus infections ,","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"Kinsa recently adapted its software","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"to detect spikes of \" atypical fever \"","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"that do not correlate with historical flu patterns","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"and are likely attributable to the coronavirus .","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"As of noon Wednesday , the company ' s live map showed fevers","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"holding steady","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"or dropping almost universally across the country , with two prominent exceptions . . .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"By Friday morning , fevers in every county in the country were on a downward trend ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"depicted in four shades of blue on the map . . .","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"As of Monday morning , more than three-quarters of the country was deep blue .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"A separate display of the collective national fever trend ,","depth":15},{"id":106,"text":"which had spiked upward to a peak on March 17 ,","depth":15},{"id":107,"text":"had fallen so far","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"that it was actually below the band","depth":16},{"id":109,"text":"showing historical flu fever trends","depth":16},{"id":110,"text":"- which meant","depth":16},{"id":111,"text":"that the lockdown has cut not only Covid-19 transmission","depth":17},{"id":112,"text":"but flu transmission , too .","depth":17},{"id":113,"text":"Those exceptions were a broad swathe of New Mexico and a ring of Louisiana parishes","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"surrounding New Orleans .","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"One catch :","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"if you ' re dealing with a severe case of the coronavirus ,","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"are you using a Kinsa thermometer ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"or is the hospital using some other one ?","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"In other words , is the Kinsa data a good way","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"to measure the milder cases ?","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"Let ' s Avoid Unneeded Confrontations with Religious Communities during This Crisis ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"Okay ?","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"The silver lining to the Hillsborough County Sheriff ' s Office","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"arresting Pastor Rodney Howard-Browne in Florida","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"is that the conflict did not escalate to a physical altercation .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Local authorities really , really , really don ' t want the River at Tampa Bay Church to hold services","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"that continue to involve large groups of people","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"getting together","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"and remaining close together , in violation of the CDC ' s \" social distancing \" recommendations .","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"If you want to persuade someone ,","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"you first have to see the world through their eyes ,","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"and understand what drives them ,","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"what motivates them ,","depth":17},{"id":134,"text":"and what they value .","depth":17},{"id":135,"text":"The moment you turn it into a contest of wills ,","depth":14},{"id":136,"text":"people dig in their heels .","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"If law enforcement has someone religious in the ranks ,","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"that might be the right person","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"to persuade someone","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"that a particular action is consistent with their religious principles .","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"The Hillsborough authorities are at least trying to assure Christian citizens","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"that temporarily suspending services is consistent with their religious values .","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"That ' s why Howard-Browne was arrested Monday on misdemeanor charges of unlawful assembly and violating quarantine orders during a public health emergency ,","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"said Hillsborough Sheriff Chad Chronister .","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"' Because of the reckless disregard of public safety","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"and after repeated requests and warnings ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"I worked with our state attorney , Andrew Warren ,","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"to obtain a warrant for unlawful assembly and violation of public health emergency rules ,","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"both of which are second degree misdemeanors , '","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"Chronister said .","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"\" Our goal here is not to stop anyone from worshiping ,","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"but the safety and well-being of our community must always come first. \"","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"Chronister and Warren held a news conference Monday","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"announcing the charges","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"before the pastor was in custody .","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"That day , the number of confirmed coronavirus cases across Florida surged past 5,700 .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"Warren then took to the lectern","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"and quoted the Bible .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"' I ' d remind the good pastor of Mark 12:31 ,","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"which said","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"there ' s no more important commandment","depth":15},{"id":162,"text":"than to love thy neighbor as thyself , '","depth":15},{"id":163,"text":"Warren said .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"' Loving your neighbors is protecting them ,","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"not jeopardizing their health","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"by exposing them to this deadly virus . '","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"Hard cases make bad law ,","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"and we are in the textbook definition of extreme circumstances .","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"In just about any other situation , the state attempting to restrict , block , or ban gatherings of religious believers","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"would be straight-up unconstitutional ,","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"no questions asked .","depth":14},{"id":172,"text":"You don ' t have to be a fervent believer","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"to be wary about state officials","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"who deem religious services as a unnecessary luxury during this crisis ,","depth":15},{"id":175,"text":"but who also insist","depth":16},{"id":176,"text":"every Planned Parenthood facility must remain open .","depth":16},{"id":177,"text":"New York City mayor Bill de Blasio ,","depth":17},{"id":178,"text":"who has managed to botch a great many decisions during this crisis ,","depth":17},{"id":179,"text":"had to go even further","depth":16},{"id":180,"text":"and threaten to permanently shut down any religious institution","depth":16},{"id":181,"text":"that violates state orders","depth":17},{"id":182,"text":"to not hold services .","depth":17},{"id":183,"text":"( He doesn ' t have that authority . )","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"Yesterday , large numbers of New Yorkers gathered in crowds","depth":16},{"id":185,"text":"that violated CDC rules","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"in order to watch the U.S. Navy hospital ship arrive at the pier .","depth":15},{"id":187,"text":"The NYPD only offered verbal warnings .","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"While the social distancing rules apply to everyone ,","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"religious groups","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"who have a preexisting tense relationship with a nonreligious mayor","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"may fairly wonder","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"if they ' re being singled out for particular enforcement .","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"In a situation such as this , state authorities would be wise to at least try to help the religious communities find alternative arrangements .","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"Here in Virginia , some churches","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"that can find the space","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"are holding \" drive-in services , \"","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"where families attend in their cars","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"and remain in their vehicles ,","depth":16},{"id":199,"text":"honking their horns in rejoice .","depth":16},{"id":200,"text":"That idea may not work in more urban environments ,","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"but you look at a problem differently","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"when you stop seeing the question as , \" How can I stop this religious community from gathering ? \"","depth":15},{"id":203,"text":"and instead see it as , \" How can I help this religious community find a way","depth":17},{"id":204,"text":"to feel a sense of connection","depth":17},{"id":205,"text":"that is safe","depth":17},{"id":206,"text":"and won ' t run afoul of the social-distancing guidelines ? \"","depth":17},{"id":207,"text":"David Koresh may have been a maniac ,","depth":15},{"id":208,"text":"but the Branch Davidians didn ' t deserve to die for their actions ,","depth":15},{"id":209,"text":"and","depth":15},{"id":210,"text":"had law enforcement understood the belief system of those inside better ,","depth":16},{"id":211,"text":"maybe that terrible outcome could have been avoided . \"","depth":16},{"id":212,"text":"While many religious scholars have differing interpretations of the event ,","depth":14},{"id":213,"text":"they agree","depth":15},{"id":214,"text":"that Waco remains the case study on how religious literacy is critical","depth":16},{"id":215,"text":"to peacefully enforcing the law in a pluralistic society ,","depth":17},{"id":216,"text":"whether dealing with apocalyptic groups like the Branch Davidians or the polygamous FLDS.","depth":17},{"id":217,"text":"\" Living in a free country means allowing people to believe things","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"that the rest of us find nutty ;","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"the question is how we figure out a way","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"that functions","depth":13},{"id":221,"text":"and abides with the law in a pluralist society .","depth":13},{"id":222,"text":"ADDENDUM :","depth":5},{"id":223,"text":"Without going into the specific numbers ,","depth":6},{"id":224,"text":"I can now say","depth":7},{"id":225,"text":"that the timeline of China ' s false statements about the coronavirus is the most-read piece","depth":8},{"id":226,"text":"I have written at in at least two years ,","depth":9},{"id":227,"text":"probably much longer .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":455,"left":229,"right":454,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":229,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":454,"left":235,"right":453,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":235,"left":2,"right":234,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":234,"left":230,"right":233,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":230,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":231,"right":232,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":231,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"N